The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | 1 killed, 2 hurt in mishaps
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      1 killed, 2 hurt in mishaps
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A woman died and two men were injured in three accidents on Thursday night. Jaya Bose, 65, died at Ramakrishna Mission Seva Pratishthan on Friday. She was hit by a car on Motilal Nehru Road. The driver was arrested. Around 10pm, Rajendra Prasad Agarwal, 42, was hit by a Matador on Lenin Sarani. He was rushed to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital with head injuries. The driver fled the spot. Md Sirajuddin, 19, was hit by an autorickshaw near Chowlpatti on Gas Street around 11.15pm. He was admitted to Calcutta Medical College and Hospital with head injuries. The driver has been arrested.        
	nHistorian dead: Historian Pradip Sinha died on Friday in his Ekdalia home after a prolonged illness. Born in 1935, Sinha began his career as a lecturer of history at Calcutta University and retired as head of the department of history at Rabindra Bharati University. Sinha wrote several books, including Calcutta in Urban History and Nineteenth Century Bengal.        
	nFatal fall: Mahesh Yadav, 35, died after falling from the ninth-floor flat on Alipore Road where he used to work as a help on Friday evening. Pipes on the second floor of the building broke his fall. Firemen brought down the body.        
	nBody found: The decomposed body of Jagai Mandal, 46, was found behind a bush at Sonarpur on Friday morning with injury marks on his neck and shoulder. Police said he had been killed.        
	nYouths arrested: Anjan Sarkar, 32, Sanjay Saha, 29, and Prabir Lodh, 30, were arrested for allegedly looting Rs 3.5 lakh from a trader on Wednesday. About Rs 3.1 lakh has been recovered from them. The trio were remanded in judicial custody.         
	nFire: A fire broke out in the ground-floor meter box of State Bank of Indias RN Mukherjee Road branch on Friday. Two tenders doused the flames in 15 minutes.        
	nPosters: Calcutta airport authorities and police tore off posters put up on the walls of domestic and international terminal buildings by the Trinamul Congress-backed Airports Authority Staff and Workers Union on Friday.                                                                                                                                                          
